race.comment: GOLD PUMA (6) returned from a brief spell and registered her fourth minor placing from seven starts when edged out over 1200m at Grafton last time. Peak rating last prep was at this trip off an inferior lead-up rating so she looks well placed to earn a well-deserved win. The query runner is debutant SINATRA (11) from the Matthew Dunn stable. Big trial winner at Ballina recently. By Microphone and is a half-brother to stakes placegetter Grinzinger Love. Sure to have plenty of admirers. FOREVER FORTUNE (2) should be ready to peak after three runs back from a break. Led and faded out of things last start at Doomben. This is easier. Suspect these three have top spot covered between them. RELEASETHEWOLVES (8) next elect third up.
